  "texts": [
    "Recent research has therefore focused on exploring and developing mechanisms to align AI systems with human values and goals.",
    "Existing approaches in the context of LLMs can be broadly split into three categories:",
    "(1) Specification-based approaches: This set of approaches involves pre-specifying a set of values and principles that an AI model should follow 24, 37, 38.",
    "A set of rules or principles is provided either to the model itself (in the case of \"constitutional AI 41 \") or to human labellers who are then tasked with identifying which responses are more aligned with these pre-specified values in different contexts.",
    "(2) Inference-based approaches: These approaches encompass methods whereby AI systems learn what values to align to implicitly through human feedback or human demonstrations."
  ],
